modules.description: This module provides direct bidirectional conversion between JavaScript promises and Lwt promises, enabling seamless interoperability between the two promise systems. It operates on `Promise.t` and `Promise_lwt.t` types, allowing values to be passed across JS and OCaml boundaries without manual wrapping. Concrete use cases include integrating Lwt-based OCaml code with JavaScript APIs that return promises, such as DOM operations or external libraries.
